    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-11-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-11-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–1152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-11-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 11, 1952—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 162. From <persName
                        corresp="#p_GROSSEA1">Gross</persName>. Re <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                        >Syg</gloss>’s resignation.</p>
                <p>At <persName corresp="#p_LUNSJMAH1">Luns</persName>’ dinner last night, <persName
                        corresp="#p_GROMYKOAA1">Gromyko</persName> asked me whether we had any
                    suggestions re <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName>’s successor. I
                    replied that <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName>’s resignation had come
                    as a surprise to me and I had not yet had an opportunity to obtain the views of
                    the <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>. I commented that the <gloss
                        target="#t_Sov1">Sov</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Del1">del</gloss> two years ago had made a number of
                    suggestions and had in fact indicated willingness to consider qualified people
                    from any area. <persName corresp="#p_GROMYKOAA1">Gromyko</persName> replied that
                    “the situation was different”.</p>
                <p>I said that we should probably consult about the question and <persName
                        corresp="#p_GROMYKOAA1">Gromyko</persName> agreed, I thought rather
                    emphatically. I thought it wise to tell him that I personally doubted we would
                    take an initiative in suggesting consultations (having in mind protection of
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Pres <persName corresp="#p_TSIANGTF1"
                        >Tsiang</persName>, although I of course did not mention this to <persName
                        corresp="#p_GROMYKOAA1">Gromyko</persName>). <persName
                        corresp="#p_GROMYKOAA1">Gromyko</persName> repeated that it would be a good
                    idea to have informal consultations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>[<persName corresp="#p_GROSSEA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gross</hi>
                                </persName>]</item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
